For the Minimization, I used the Insane script to build my bilayer + pfda system, then I added 1 NA.  

Building the Bilayer system with Insane: 

insane -o system.gro -f pf10c_em.gro -l DOPC -sol W -salt 0 -p topol.top

The -f option specifies the input structure for the pfda. -l specifies which phospholipid to add to the 
membrane. -sol specifies the solvent. -salt specifies whether or not to add NA and CL ions; if the 
parameter is 0, then ions will be added to make the system neutral, whereas a positive number will indicate
molarity. For example, -salt 0.15 will add NA and CL atoms to set the salt concentration = 0.15.


Adding 1 NA:

For some reason, using -salt 0 in the insane command does not neutralize the -1 charge on the pfda. So I 
manually added one sodium, NA, ion to the system. 

gmx grompp -f inputs/min.mdp -c system.gro -p topology/topol.top -o min.tpr
gmx genion -s min.tpr -p topology/topol.top -o finalsystem.gro -pname NA -neutral


Minimization:

After adding 1 NA, we now have our final system, with pfda, DOPC, W, and NA. I now did an energy 
minimization using the mdp file min.mdp.

gmx grompp -f inputs/min.mdp -c finalsystem.gro -p topology/topol.top -o finalsystem.tpr
gmx mdrun -s finalsystem.tpr -v -deffnm finalsystem_min

You should get two files called finalsystem_min.gro (which is the structure of the minimized system) and 
finalsystem_min.log which has the output results of the energy minimization. The next step is to perform
an equilibration. 
